OL,3,CHomeless and rough sleepers offered
OL,4,Cshelter as temperatures drop in London
OL,6,FLondon's Severe Weather Emergency
OL,7,FProtocol (SWEP) has been activated for
OL,8,Fthe first time this year, meaning
OL,9,Fthose sleeping on the streets will be
OL,10,Foffered accommodation as protection
OL,11,Ffrom freezing weather conditions.
OL,13,FSWEP is launched when temperatures are
OL,14,Fforecast to fall to 0C or below.
OL,16,FLondon boroughs will be encouraged to
OL,17,Fprovide emergency shelter, alongside
OL,18,Fhomelessness charities.
